INSERT INTO us_coins (numista_id, name, years, composition, description) VALUES (298883, '1 Dollar "American Silver Eagle" New Reverse (Bullion Coin)', '2021 - 2022', 'Silver (.999)', 'Introduced in 1986, the popular and now-iconic American Eagle Silver Proof Coins are collector versions of the official United States Mint American Eagle Silver Bullion Coins. The classic Walking Liberty design by Adolph A. Weinman featured on the coin’s obverse has long been a collector favorite. After 35 years, this famous design has been refreshed. Thanks to technological advancements in the design and minting process, Liberty now encompasses some of Weinman’s original details that were not previously possible. For the 2021 coin, the United States Mint returned to its original historical assets to render a closer reflection of Weinman’s original vision that includes the addition of his traditional artist mark. The reverse design is new. To give the new coins an added level of security, they have also been updated with enhanced security features, including a reeded edge variation. The new reverse design features an eagle as it approaches a landing, carrying an oak branch as if to add it to a nest. ');
